text: Kazangulovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kazangulovsky Selsoviet, Davlekanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 441 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 24 km from Davlekanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Davlekanovsky District
title: Kazangulovo
